<br>
couple of pounds of meat.  beef, venison, mutton, etc.<br>
potatos<br>
onions<br>
mushrooms<br>
any other veggies you like.  <br>
Spicy V-8<br>
<br>
tobasco<br>
cayenne<br>
black pepper<br>
minced garlic<br>
salt<br>
Tony Chachere's<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Cut meat into bite sized cubes.  <br>
Cut enough onion to add flavor to meat.  I like cooked onions, so I put a good bit.<br>
Put meat and onion in a pot.<br>
Add tobasco, cayenne, Tony's, black pepper, minced garlic, salt.  All to taste.<br>
Brown meat on all sides.<br>
Set off burner once meat is browned.<br>
Peel potatos and cut into bite size chunks.<br>
Prepare all other veggies in same fashion.<br>
Dump veggies in pot w/ meat.<br>
Cover w/ Spicy V-8.  Some veggies have a high water content.  If soup is too thick, then add water, but wait until the veggies cook a little. I hate thin soup.  )<br>
<br>
Simmer until  potatos are soft.  Taste often and season to your personal taste.<br>
<br>
Great for cold weather!  \;-)<br>
