<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3 or 4 cloves garlic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, coarsely chopped<br>
<br>
Cook till the meat is browned. DO NOT DRAIN! If you got a good lean cut, there won't be much fat anyway.<br>
<br>
Put it into your crockpot, you do have a crockpot? and add:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 can diced tomatoes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 4oz(?) can tomato paste</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, you know, the little can<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp oregano</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp cocoa</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp cumin</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp salt</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp black pepper</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tsp cayenne</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tbsp chili powder</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1/4 cup water</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Now, some try to be cute and leave out the cumin or cocoa, but without them it's not chili, so don't do it.  Or...well...just don't.<br>
<br>
Simmer for about 8 hours.  Add a can of drained dark red kidney beans 15 minutes before you serve.<br>
<br>
Ways to make it better:<br>
1. Simmer for 24 hours, then refrigerate for 24 hours.  Reheat in crockpot, add beans, enjoy the best damn chili you ever tasted.  Be sure to add some more water before you simmer it this long, a little bit at a time.<br>
