<br>
Homemade Pizza<br>
<br>
1 pkg of dry yeast<br>
1/2 cup of milk<br>
1/4 cup of crisco<br>
1/2 teas. of salt<br>
1 1/2 cups of all purpose flour<br>
Tomato sauce<br>
Shredded Mozzerella<br>
Oregano<br>
Italian Seasoning<br>
Garlic Powder<br>
Toppings<br>
<br>
<br>
1 pkg dry yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup of WARM water.  Too hot or too cold will kill yeast.<br>
1/2 cup of scalded milk.  I scald mine in the microwave.  Scald means a thin film on top.  Do NOT boil.<br>
1/4 cup of Crisco disolved in milk.  Let cool til WARM and add to yeast mixture.<br>
1/2 teas. of salt to mixture.<br>
1 1/2 cup of all purpose flour.  Add to mix.  Add flour til dough is not sticky.<br>
Leave in bowl about 20 min.  I use a heavy stone bowl and cover it with a towel.  Make sure bowl is in a fairly warm place.  NOT the oven, or you will have bread instead of pizza dough.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Once dough rises, spread out on your cooking stone or in a shallow pan.  Make sure you stretch the dough up the sides.  You want to make a shallow bowl.  Apply tomato sauce evenly across dough.  Sprinkle with Seasonings.  Layer pizza toppings.  Do NOT make your pizza higher than the edges of your pan!!  It is HELL to clean out of the oven when it overflows!!<br>
<br>
Bake @ 375 for 15 to 20 minutes.  Keep an eye on it.  Baking time will flucuate with altitude and depth of toppings.<br>
<br>
Meat prep for beef and sausage:  Lightly brown ground beef and sausage in a skillet.  Sprinkle beef with Tony's liberally.  I also add some diced onions to the skillet while browning.  Crumble and add to layers of pizza.  If you don't brown it first, you will burn the pizza trying to get it to cook.<br>
<br>
You can also add shrimp and crawfish to this mix!<br>
<br>
We haven't ordered a pizza in over a year because of this receipe!  <br>
