But I was surprised, shocked and saddened to read the line &quot;the late Paul Prudhomme&quot;.  When did this happen?  Where was I?<br>
<br>
I was in New Orleans on a business trip in the late 80s and had the pleasure of eating at his restaurant.  My companions and I waited in line (camped!) almost 3 hours, since we did not have reservations (I don't recall if reservations were even accepted).  We survived having to inch by the cat house that was located on the same street as the restaurant (at least a million cats prowling about the yard, and the stench to go along with them -- ugh).  We were entertained by street performers, and made friends with others in line.<br>
<br>
